11/12/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Italian and Albanian customs will introduce an integrated system of services, according to a joint statement by Albanian Customs Director General Sokol Kraja and his Italian counterpart Mario Andrea Guaiana. They met Tuesday (10 December) in Tirana. Italian authorities have trained the majority of Albanian customs officers, more than 600 agents, as a result of bilateral agreements signed between 1997 and 1999. (AlbanianNews - 11/12/02; ATA - 10/12/02)
